    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-02-26T16:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-02-26T15:49:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <head>139. Summary of Conclusions of a Meeting of the Washington Special Actions
                        Group<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d139fn1">Source: National Archives,
                            <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box H–115, <gloss
                            target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> Meetings Minutes, Originals, 1971. Top
                        Secret; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1">Nodis</gloss>. The meeting took place in
                        the Situation Room of the White House.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1971-02-26T15:49:00-05:00" to="1971-02-26T16:32:00-05:00">February
                            26, 1971, 3:49–4:32 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Laos</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPATION</head>
                    <item>Chairman—<persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>State <list>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_SWH1"
                                    >William Sullivan</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>Defense <list>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PD1">David Packard</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Rear Adm. <persName corresp="#p_FWR1">William R.
                                    Flanagan</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>
                        <list>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Richard Helms</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_NWE1">William Nelson</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>
                        <list>
                            <item>Lt. Gen. <persName corresp="#p_VJW1">John W. Vogt</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Staff <list>
                            <item>Col. <persName corresp="#p_KRT1">Richard T. Kennedy</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HJH1">John H. Holdridge</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName>D. Keith Guthrie</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">SUMMARY OF CONCLUSIONS</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Lao <gloss target="#t_SGU1">SGU</gloss>s</hi>. The <gloss
                            target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> endorsed the plan submitted by the field
                        calling for diversion of four Lao <gloss target="#t_SGU1">SGU</gloss>s from
                        Operation Oklahoma City to the southern edge of the Plaine des Jarres north
                        of Ban Na.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Thai <gloss target="#t_SGU1">SGU</gloss>s</hi>. The <gloss
                            target="#t_WSAG1">WSAG</gloss> requested immediate assessments of: <list>
                            <label>(a)</label>
                            <item>the comparative military advantages of employment of Thai <gloss
                                    target="#t_SGU1">SGU</gloss>s or Thai regular troops in the
                                defense of Long Tieng.</item>
                            <label>(b)</label>
                            <item>the legal issues involved in the use of Thai regular troops at
                                Long Tieng.</item>
                            <label>(c)</label>
                            <item>the relative advantages of the two alternative plans proposed by
                                the field for utilization of Thai <gloss target="#t_SGU1"
                                    >SGU</gloss>s to defend Long Tieng. This assessment should be
                                based on appropriate consultation with the field and with the Thai
                                Government.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Air Support</hi>. The <gloss target="#t_WSAG1"
                            >WSAG</gloss> directed preparation of a survey of available Thai and US
                        assets for air support of friendly troops in North Laos.</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here are the minutes of the meeting.]</p>
            </div>
